HEADWORD: Inadequacy
<hw>In*ad"e*qua*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Inadequate</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
inadequate or insufficient; defectiveness; insufficiency;
inadequateness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>inadequacy</qex> and consequent inefficacy of the alleged
causes.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. T. Dwight.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

